  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate whether a new model of health care for chronic
      patients, based on Case Management and guided by a nurse which targets the patient´s risk, is
      more effective than usual care at Primary Health care in Chile. Additionally, this
      intervention would provide a better quality of care and a more efficient health provision.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
